# Git Commit Automation Rule

## Rule Configuration

```json
{
  "name": "git-commit-automation",
  "description": "Automates git commit process when tasks are completed",
  "triggers": {
    "file_changes": {
      "patterns": ["src/**/*", "tests/**/*"]
    }
  },
  "actions": [
    {
      "type": "commit",
      "message_template": "[TASK-XXX] Type: Brief description\n\nDetails about changes\n\nCloses TASK-XXX",
      "variables": {
        "TASK-XXX": "extract_task_id",
        "Type": "determine_commit_type",
        "description": "generate_description"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "push",
      "branch": "current_branch"
    }
  ],
  "conditions": {
    "task_status": "[x]",
    "has_tests": true,
    "coverage_threshold": 80,
    "files_changed": true
  }
}
```

## Commit Types

- `feat`: New feature
- `fix`: Bug fix
- `docs`: Documentation changes
- `test`: Test updates
- `refactor`: Code refactoring
- `style`: Code style changes
- `chore`: Maintenance tasks

